.TH "tb_port_add_nfc_credits" 9 "tb_port_add_nfc_credits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_port_add_nfc_credits \- add/remove non flow controlled credits to port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tb_port_add_nfc_credits
.BI "(struct tb_port *port "  ","
.BI "int credits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
Port to add/remove NFC credits
.IP "credits" 12
Credits to add/remove
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Change the number of NFC credits allocated to \fIport\fP by \fIcredits\fP. To remove
NFC credits pass a negative amount of credits.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns 0 on success or an error code on failure.
